0009|- [HelpText]
0010|*To help the user, the Survo system provides a special inquiry system.
0011|*By entering various keywords, information on Survo operations and
0012|*other relevant facts will be displayed in the Help window.
0014|*To make an inquiry, a keyword followed by a question mark (like EDITOR?
0015|*PRINT? PLOT? ) is typed on any empty line in the edit field and
0016|*activated either by the mouse (double-click) or by the ESC key.
0017|*All pertinent information will then be displayed. After return to
0018|*normal editing mode, the previous situation in the edit field will be
0019|*restored. However, in inquiries about Survo operations it is typical
0020|*that a general pattern of the operation in question will be printed
0021|*on the inquiry line.
0022|*If the keyword is not found, a list of related keywords having the
0023|*same forepart will be listed and any of them may be selected.
0025|*An inquiry may be started also by pressing the F1 (HELP) key. Then
0026|*information on the last operation activated may be obtained directly.
0027|*Still another way to start an inquiry is to activate a word in the
0028|*edit field by the keys F2 F1 or by a double-click of the rightmost
0029|*mouse button.
0031|*In the Help Window, the system often suggests related or more specific
0032|*information which may be selected by keystrokes or by the mouse.
0033|*It is then possible to discover various functions of Survo.
0035|*After any branch to a new topic, it is possible to return back to
0036|*previous displays step by step by pressing BACKSPACE (or clicking Prev).
0037|*At any stage during an inquiry, new keywords may be suggested first
0038|*by pressing `?' and then entering the keyword.
0039|*An alternative way to select other keywords in the Help Window is to
0040|*move the cursor by arrow keys (or mouse) and activate by by ESC (or mouse).
0042|*Each display presented by the inquiry system may also be
0043|*copied in the edit field by pressing `+' .
0044|*The newest options are often highlighted.
0046|*Other ways for getting information from the inquiry system of Survo
0047|*are provided by the sucro commands /HSEARCH and /HLIST.
