0119|- [HelpText]
0120|*Survo is an integrated system for statistical analysis, computing,
0121|*data base management, graphics, desktop publishing, etc.
0122|SThrough its unique editorial interface, Survo forms a general
S   |                    4444444444444444444
0123|*environment for many kinds of applications.
0124|*Technically, Survo is a collection of C programs (modules) with a common
0125|*interface established by the Survo Editor, a general text editor.
0126|*During a Survo session the editor calls Survo modules automatically
0127|*according to the user's activations. The user has no need to know
0128|*how the programs are linked together. He/she sees Survo as one
0129|*integrated environment.
0130|*Currently Survo includes over 100 C programs (.EXE files) and
0131|*hundreds of other system files. All these files are located in one
0132|*directory <Survo> and in its subdirectories.
S   |           <     >
0133|*Typically <Survo>=C:\PROGRA~1\SURVO.
S   |           <     >
