0144|- [HelpText]
0145|*When EDITOR is in use, all information (text, data, results and
0146|*operations) is represented in an edit field which consists, for
0147|*example, of 100 columns and 1000 rows (lines). On the left side of
0148|*the field the line numbers and a control column (originally filled
0149|*with asterisks *) are displayed.
0150|*The edit field is always partially visible on the CRT which is like
0151|*a window to the field. The user can scroll text on the screen to any
0152|*direction by the arrow keys and by the PREV and NEXT keys.
0154|*The size of the field may be altered by a REDIM operation.
0155|*the contents of the field is saved in an edit file by a SAVE oper-
0156|*ation and the edit file is reloaded to the field by a LOAD operation.
0157|*Also several fields or parts of them as well those of any text files
0158|*can be combined by a SHOW operation.
0160|*Selected lines of the edit field are printed on the paper by a PRINT
0161|*operation. PRINT has also an extended form permitting printing of
0162|*parts of several edit files in any order as an entire document
0163|*which is automatically divided into pages, etc.
