0209|*Making hypertext applications in Survo
0211|*The inquiry (help) system is a hypertext. One can activate any word
0212|*in the edit field by the key combination F2 F1. If the word is a valid
0213|*keyword, the inquiry system will display information related to it.
0214|*While reading help text, one can also move the cursor, indicate another
0215|*keyword and activate an inquiry for it by ESC (or F2 F1), etc.
0216|*All the help texts are stored in edit files on the path defined by
0217|*the system parameter qpath in the SURVO.APU file.
0218|*This path (and the help texts) can be changed by the QPATH command.
0220|*Thus it is possible to create and maintain several hypertexts related
0221|*to any topic by the same method as we are doing in the inquiry system
0222|*of Survo.
0223|*To see how the edit files are organized in order to support help
0224|*texts and menus, study the edit files of the help system, please.
