0314|- [/New]
0316|*Files made by other programs as well as websites can be opened
0317|*while working in Survo simply by activating (path)names of files
0318|*and website addresses appearing within the text in the edit field.
0319|- shadow W: [LINK(http://www.survo.fi)] [/LINK]
0320|*For example, the website of Survo is opened by activating www.survo.fi
S   |                                                           WWWWWWWWWWWW
0321|*by the double-click or by the ESC key.
0322|*Similarly, when activating a filename of a PDF file, say D:\PAPERS\DOC1.PDF,
0323|*Survo calls the START command of the Windows command interpreter
0324|*to open this file by the program (typically Adobe Acrobat) associated
0325|*to this filetype (see in Windows 'Folder options' -> 'File types').
S   |                                                    >
0327|*Typical filetypes of Survo like edit files (.EDT), data files (.SVO),
0328|*matrix files (.MAT), etc. can be browsed by activating their pathnames
0329|*typed in the edit field using suitable 'show' commands.
0331|*Please note that if an edit line containing a link word starts by a valid
0332|*Survo command word, the command is always activated in the first place.
0334|*Associations described above are defined in a Survo system file OPEN.SYS.
0335|*More details (for advanced users) on the next page!
