0394|- [New]
0395|*Detecting errors in command and specification words
0396|- [/New]
0398|*When a command is activated and it does not correspond to any known
0399|*Survo operation, an error message is displayed.
0400|*If the command word is close enough to some real Survo commands,
0401|*the error message includes a list of possible alternatives
0402|*thus guiding the user to detect a typo etc.
0403|*The alternative commands are found by computing the Levenshtein (edit)
0404|*distance d between the given command and each possible real command
0405|*and listing the command words having the shortest distance.
0406|*The list of alternatives is shown when d<3 and there are less than 6
S   |                                         <
0407|*words in the list.
0408|*In Survo, Levenshtein distance is slightly modified by permitting inter-
0409|- shadow %: [LINK(q0c_08.html)] [/LINK]
0410|*change of two consecutive letters in the edit operations (see STRDIST?).
S   |                                                               %%%%%%%
0412|*Specification words:
0413|*By default, specification words are not checked.
0414|*Checking them is turned on by the command
0415|*SYSTEM spec_check=1 (or by the soft buttons SYSTEM -> SPEC).
S   |                                                     >
0416|*When a Survo operation is activated and checking is on, all pertinent
0417|*specification words (like HOME in HOME=200,300) are compared to
0418|*a list of all specification words usable in that operation.
0419|*If a specification word does not correspond to any allowed word
0420|*and Levenshtein distance to the closest one is less than 3 and
0421|*there are not more than 5 such words, an error message (containing
0422|*a list of alternative words) is displayed and the operation is
0423|*interrupted.
0425|*Since the user may have his/her own specifications which are not
0426|*relevant in the current operation but resemble some actual
0427|*specifications, this procedure may sometimes lead to false alarms.
0428|*Therefore it is advisable to turn spec_check on only after encountering
0429|*difficulties in activation. Checking may then discover typos etc.
0430|E
